le our University as a whole to effectively manage potential exposures facing faculty, staff, students and visitors through the sharing of knowledge, education, and training.  Our main responsibilities include:  Identifying and analyzing risks Implementing and evaluating loss control techniques Mitigating risks through insurance policies Our insurance consist of a wide range of risks such as Athletic Injury, Programs for Minors, Workers' Compensation, General Liability, Automobile, Mobile Equipment and Certificates of Insurance including a Tenant User Liability Insurance Program (TULIP) associated with special events.  Notary Publics are also available across campus for University business use.  Please contact the Risk Management office for guidance with your insurance needs at 940-565-2109.   Contact Us: Risk Management Services 700 North Texas Blvd Denton, Texas 76203 Denton, TX 76203-5017 USA Voice: (940) 565-2109 http://riskmanagement.unt.edu/ Email us: Have questions on content or technical issues? Please contact us. jonathan.dowd@unt.edu UNT System: UNT Home UNT System UNT Dallas UNT Health Science Center Site last updated on April 21, 2017 Disclaimer | AA/EOE/ADA | Privacy Statement | Web Accessibility Policy | State of Texas Online | Emergency Preparedness 